ment. More than a collection of cartoons, this book connects comics with fundamentals of health communication and discusses why the form can be uniquely effective for these purposes. Each chapter focuses on the use of graphic public health in the context of four specific goals: health literacy, risk communication, health promotion, and advocacy. Li-Vollmer also includes guidance for practitioners getting started in creating comics for any form of public information, and especially for public health.Practical and purposeful, Graphic Public Health is a clarion call for the current era and an invaluable resource for public health professionals and advocates, scholars of comics and graphic studies, and fans of the graphic medicine genre.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aHealth education. 7aMEDICAL / Public Health.2bisacsh  aComics.  aGuide to creating comics for public information.  aadvocacy.  acartoonist.  acommunication.  agraphic medicine.  agraphica.  ahealth literacy.  ahealth promotion.  apandemic.  apublic health.  arisk communication.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022 Englishz978311099389908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE COMPLETE 2022z9783110994810oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022 Englishz978311099319608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Medicine and Life Sciences 2022z9783110993134oZDB-23-DPM08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertPenn State University Press Complete eBook-Package 2022z97831107669290 cprintz978027109325340uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9780271093833?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780271093833423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780271093833